{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Pseudo-clase","mdn_url":"/es/docs/Glossary/Pseudo-class","locale":"es","native":"Español","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>En CSS, un selector de&nbsp;<strong>pseudo-clase&nbsp;</strong>apunta a elementos dependiendo de&nbsp;su estado en lugar de en su información en el arbol del documento. Por ejemplo, el selector <code>a</code><a href=\"/es/docs/Web/CSS/:visited\"><code>:visited</code></a> aplica estilos solamente a los links que el usuario ha visitado.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"aprender_más","title":"Aprender más","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"referencía_técnica","title":"Referencía técnica","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Pseudo-classes\">Pseudo-class documentación</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Aprender más","id":"aprender_más"}],"summary":"En CSS, un selector de pseudo-clase apunta a elementos dependiendo de su estado en lugar de en su información en el arbol del documento. Por ejemplo, el selector a:visited aplica estilos solamente a los links que el usuario ha visitado.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Pseudo-class","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Pseudo-classe","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Pseudo-class","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Pseudo-class","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"伪类","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"es/glossary/pseudo-class","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/es/glossary/pseudo-class/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/es/docs/Glossary","title":"Glosario"},{"uri":"/es/docs/Glossary/Pseudo-class","title":